<recipe>
	<title>Banana Bread</title>
	<meta>
		<dishtype>Breads</dishtype>
		<dishtype>Quick Breads</dishtype>
		<comment>I'm not a banana person, but a roommate generating lots of overripe leftover bananas prompted me to develop a recipe. I think this one is pretty good. The whole wheat and oat flour help balance the flavour and render slightly more healthy what is essentially a cake. The oat flour can be substituted for more whole wheat, or both can be substituted for white.</comment>
	</meta>
